libisoburn
------------------------------------------
libisoburn is a frontend for libraries libburn and libisofs which enables
creation and expansion of ISO-9660 filesystems on all CD/DVD/BD media
supported by libburn. This includes media like DVD+RW, which do not support
multi-session management on media level and even plain disk files or block
devices.

The price for that is thorough specialization on data files in ISO-9660
filesystem images. So libisoburn is not suitable for audio (CD-DA) or any
other CD layout which does not entirely consist of ISO-9660 sessions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.9-1
  libburn4-1.1.6-1bl1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-2
  libiconv2-1.14-2
  libisofs6-1.1.6-1bl1
  libreadline7-6.1.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cygport-0.10.5-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-2
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://libburnia-project.org/

Canonical download:
  http://files.libburnia-project.org/releases/libisoburn-1.1.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libisoburn-1.1.6-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libisoburn-1.1.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libisoburn-1.1.6-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libisoburn-1.1.6-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libisoburn1-1.1.6-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libisoburn-devel-1.1.6-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

